data.name: Out of Denmark Restaurant
data.description:
Each meal begins with complimentary Danish appetizers including Home Cured Salmon, carved to order in the dining room, and Danish Koldt Bord, steamed mussels in mustard garlic sauce and deviled egg with caviar, presented in a traditional Danish manner. The Danish Koldt Bord features pickled North Sea herring in tomato & sherry wine, boneless chicken in Madras curry with apples, celery and walnuts; marinated artichoke hearts vinaigrette, warm “Chicago” spinach dip with Danish blue cheese, marinated fresh bottom mushrooms with Dijon mustard and fresh thyme, whole petit pickled beets, and sliced fresh European cucumber salad, sweet & sour with fresh dill and herbs. Soup of the Day or Caesar Salad are also served free of charge.
Favorite seafood dishes include Snapper en Papilotte (in the bag) with wild mushrooms, leeks, shallots, red onions, carrots and Nouilly Prat Vermouth. Other specialties from the sea include Colossal Shrimp Scampi, and Grilled Salmon, which is almond crusted.

data.name: Steak 'n Shake
data.description: Steak ‘n Shake was founded in February, 1934 in Normal, Illinois. Gus Belt, Steak ‘n Shake’s founder, pioneered the concept of premium burgers and milk shakes. The Steak 'n Shake name has been symbolic of its heritage. The word “steak” stood for STEAKBURGER. The term “shake” stood for hand-dipped MILK SHAKES. Gus was determined to serve his customers the finest burgers and shakes in the business. To prove his point that his burgers were exceptionally prime, he would wheel in a barrel of steaks (including round, sirloin, and T-bones) and grind the meat into burgers right in front of the guests. Hence arose the origin of our famous slogan, “In Sight It Must Be Right.” After 79 years, we are continuing Steak n Shake’s tradition of serving the country’s best, freshest, and tastiest burgers and shakes.

data.name: Eclectic Eats Restaurant Lounge & Garden
data.description:
"We do international cuisine our own way"
By Trying our Multiple Course meals, you will experience a unique miscellany of tastes and aromas that bring the world to your plate. We've married our French Mediterranean techniques with our love of exploring various food cultures and methods. Our result was an Eclectic Fusion Cuisine crafted with the world's best approaches.

"This is an indoor/outdoor lounge with a history" 
Located on Federal Highway, Eclectic Eats is worthy of a scenic route towards a wholesome experience. Our outdoor lounge is a relaxing getaway where you can rediscover your love for food. Our vintage venue used to be one of the first diners in Delray. Legend has it that it was a frequent pit stop for Al Capone as he used to travel the East Coast during the prohibition.

"Our identity is our beliefs"
We're a team of Delray locals seeking perfection from all angles. This team is built around good old family values, and as a guest you will be engulfed with the familial vibes as we collaborate to present to you the best culinary experience possible. We believe in seeking perfection, rather than perfection itself which cannot be obtained. This keeps us motivated to present the highest standards in "Eclectic Fusion cuisine".

Can't get any greener Our approach to sustainability is a combination of positivity, organic lifestyle and innovation that seeks to research and apply sustainable solutions to environmental challenges. Our Organic Garden is a unique continuous experiment of organic horticulture practices married to sustainability concepts and techniques. For example, we irrigate only with rainwater harvested on our premise, while we recharge ground water with the surplus. Exotic herbs such as Thai basil, precious saffron and chocolate mint thrive in this organic and sustainable environment. Maintenance practices of our second Ornamental Garden is also geared towards environmental protection and sustainability.  This makes both gardens a healthy habitat of animals and birds frequently visiting us. 

We're socially responsible Dining at Eclectic Eats will contribute to a charity of your choice. We've collaborated with organizations like No Kid Hungry and Habitat for Humanity, and we are continuously raising awareness on humane causes such as child health and the environment.

“The beauty of life is that, all you have to do is just imagine to create”  - Leo Khoury, Founding Chef & Team Eclectic Member

data.name: Smoke BBQ
data.description:
Smoke BBQ (eatbbqnow.com), formerly known as Union, has just opened at 8 East Atlantic Avenue in Delray Beach. The new concept will feature authentic Kansas City style, smokehouse BBQ -- low and slow smoked meats, including burnt ends.  They will also feature Carolina pulled pork, affordable entrée selections, a cool, casual ‘American backyard’ design, a large craft beer selection, exceptional Happy Hour promotions, and a Pitmaster whose BBQ credentials are world-renowned. 

SMOKE BBQ is owned by local restaurateurs, Stephen Chin and Scott Kennedy.Executive Chef and Pitmaster Bryan Tyrell is formerly of the famed Oklahoma Joe's in Kansas City, Mo. (Anthony Bourdain named it “One of the 13 places to eat before you die”); and Bodean's BBQ in London. Tyrell is an original member of Kansas City’s Slaughterhouse Five, and is a member of the two-time American Royal Grand Champion team in the World Series of BBQ.

“Bryan Tyrell is not only the most experienced and successful competitive BBQ Pitmaster living in South Florida, but likely the entire state,” said Kennedy. “We’re thrilled he has brought his award-winning talents to Atlantic Avenue.”SMOKE BBQ will feature 15-hour oak smoked beef brisket, spare ribs, chicken, turkey and pulled pork, smoked each day using dry rubs.  The restaurant will also offer Kansas City classic burnt ends on Wednesdays (while they last.)  Additionally, SMOKE BBQ will have fresh fish and vegetarian options.  Cocktails will be made with quality purees and house-made simple syrups—all at affordable prices. 

Bryan Tyrell began his love affair with barbeque when former college roommate, Jeff Stehney, introduced him to the world of competitive BBQ in the late 1980’s.  In 1990, Bryan became a member of Slaughterhouse Five, a competitive BBQ team.  

Slaughterhouse Five went on to be one of the most successful competitive BBQ teams in the U.S., winning the 1993 American Royal - Open Division and 1995 American Royal - Invitational Division--long considered the World Championship of BBQ.  

"For me, smoking meat is a passion and an art form. Good barbecue is a feeling; it's a touch, a feel, a taste, and understanding that has been earned from years of experience. My philosophy is, why do something if it's not going to be great?” Tyrell said.

SMOKE BBQ will be open 6 days a week (closing on Tuesdays). Happy Hour will continue in its former Union tradition, with the best deals on the Ave. Happy Hours are: Mondays, Wednesday, Thursday and Saturday hours 5-7 pm; Fridays 5-8 pm; and Sundays all day. On premises corporate BBQ events and catering are also available.  Delivery Dudes will be the preferred delivery option. 
 
SMOKE BBQ has the largest screen in a restaurant in Palm Beach County, and two additional oversized projections screens to watch college games on Saturdays and NFL games on Sundays.  The restaurant will feature live music several nights a week.  The kitchen will close at 10:00 p.m. for late night dancing.  Food will be available until 1:45 a.m. with a late night snack menu.
 
For more information, call 561-330-4236 or visit www.eatbbqnow.com. Connect with SMOKE BBQ on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram. #SmokeBBQFL

data.name: Hudson at Waterway East
data.description:
The historic Old Calypso space has been transformed into an exciting new waterfront eatery and bar overlooking the Intracoastal Waterway in downtown Delray Beach with the arrival of Hudson at Waterway East. This casually hip and trendy venue features unique spaces, including alluring nooks for dining and socializing, and an expansive covered deck, amid 7,000-square-feet of waterfront bliss. 

Hudson features an innovative, seafood-centric dining menu carefully created by executive chef, season 9 Hell’s Kitchen winner Paul Niedermann. With a focus on creating seasonality in his dishes, Niedermann uses only quality ingredients such as all-natural meats, local produce and fresh, daily-caught fish.

Our team is well versed in all aspects of the restaurant business, with a particular interest in the fusion of flavors and plate presentation. Our chef-made offerings range from soups, salads and shareable starters to sandwiches and entrees. Children’s “Youngins” menu also available.

Hudson has been designed by Pam Manhas of Manhas Design and feature an eclectic, vintage-inspired aesthetic, comprising plenty of woods, tile work and brick. The open floor plan provides a variety of indoor and outdoor seating areas—including booths, high-top tables, elevated seating and bar seating—all of which offer great water views from every angle. Special features include a pizza oven and an exposed glass-front keg cooler.

There is something exciting for everyone on the urban comfort food menu, available for lunch and dinner seven days a week. With a focus on local producers and fresh ingredients, offerings range from soups, salads and shareable starters to sandwiches and entrees. The beverage program is focused on small-producer beers, spirits and wine. Modern renditions of classic cocktails, barrel-aged spirits and handcrafted cordials are some highlights of Hudson’s beverage program.

data.name: The Porch - Delray Beach
data.description:
Newly opened on January 27th, 2014, by restauranteur team Pamela Lomba and Heinrich Lowenberg. The Porch is located in Delray’s historic Blank House, built in 1907 and carefully restored, with beautiful, hardwood floors, a sunny-yellow exterior and an expansive wood deck just added to the garden area so that guests may enjoy dining indoors or out in the beautiful South Florida weather.

Co-owners of two other restaurants, “Cafe Via Flora” on Worth Avenue in Palm Beach, winner of 2012′s “Best New Business” award by the Palm Beach Chamber of Commerce and open year-round, as well as “Rustico at The Log Cabin”, open for summer season in Highlands, North Carolina, Pamela & Heinrich have over twenty years of experience in the restaurant and hospitality industry. In the last few years, they often found themselves driving out of the Palm Beach area, continuously searching for other inspiring and sophisticated dining areas in South Florida. Their affinity grew quickly for Delray’s wide array of dining choices with enthusiastic owners and staff, impressive cuisine and bold interior design concepts. It wasn’t long before the planning and excitement began at the idea of becoming a part of downtown Delray’s robust culinary community.

For The Porch, located in this special, historic venue long-treasured by the town, Pamela and Heinrich wanted to bring their very best, patron-favorite recipes created & gathered over the years from around the world to the residents and visitors of Delray Beach.

In an elegant atmosphere, using the very best ingredients, the owners aim to keep a casual and comfortable feel for everyone. Whether stopping by for a glass of wine on the outdoor deck or joining us for dinner, we welcome you and hope you enjoy…

data.description: Since we opened our first restaurant in Boardman, OH,  in 1964, we’ve been serving quality meats on handcrafted sandwiches. We call this transformation from a cut of meat to a delicious sandwich “Meatcraft™”, and our dedication to Meatcraft™ informs every decision we make. From the sandwiches we serve to our curly fries, shakes and sides, everything we do is in service to the meats. It’s why we get to work every morning at 8 a.m. even though we don't open until 11. Good food takes time to prepare, and we’re happy to put in the time to make your meal great.

Racks Fish House + Oyster Bar
data.description:
Creative in design, concept and menu, RACKS Fish House + Oyster Bar opened its doors at the beginning of 2013. 
In keeping with founder Gary Rack’s goal of establishing an unprecedented culture of restaurant dining experiences, the Delray Beach establishment sources a variety of inspiration for all aspects of its presentation. A New England seafood house featuring prohibition-style cocktails and Grand Central Oyster Bar-inspired steam kettles, RACKS Fish House + Oyster Bar will feature a unique, nouveau-nautical décor along with a responsibly sourced ocean-to-table menu that excites and inspires. 
Culinary Director Matthew Danaher, known for his straightforward style of cooking, has developed an innovative menu that incorporates beloved classics with the modern style and appetite of South Florida. Guests will discover ever-evolving recipes for Ipswich clams, oysters Rockefeller, pan roasts and po-boys as well as an extensive live raw bar featuring what’s fresh and in season.
Housed in a historic VFW building originally built in 1948, RACKS Fish House + Oyster Bar has restored the establishment to include hand-painted brick walls; a vivid raw bar displaying the day’s fresh and responsibly sourced catches as well as the restaurant’s signature custom-designed steam kettles; a zinc-topped bar exhibiting the best of American craftsmanship and lush seating paired with nautically-inspired tables.

data.name: Captain Clay and Sons Fish Market (official)
data.description: Captain Clay and Sons Fish Market is a friendly, family owned, and SUSTAINABLE  business with the freshest local fish period! We get new product in daily so we always recommend calling to see what JUST came in because dealing with all local fish (with exceptions of Salmon, Sea Bass, etc.) we don't have unlimited supply of anything. Due to the constant flow of supply we also make our own fresh Smoked Fish Dip out of the finest fresh fish, it's alway a different blend and is ALWAYS all hand cut, slow smoked, nothing processed nor preserved! Try it!
